description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting and unique opportunity to join a new team that is helping to shape mental health services for the 2.5 million people of West Yorkshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead the contracting function for the Provider Collaborative (PC), within the commissioning team and support the strategic development of the three PCs in West Yorkshire. Ensuring that clinical services put service users’ needs at the centre, are safe, focused on wellbeing and recovery, and are well led.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The contract manager role will be hosted by Leeds and York Partnership NHS Foundation Trust, but will operate across the West Yorkshire health and care system. The commissioning team you will be part of operates independently of individual NHS organisations, responsible to the Executive Directors of Lead Providers, and to the West Yorkshire Specialised Mental Health, Learning Disabilities and Autism Programme Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with a range of clinical and programme leads across the PCs and West Yorkshire, as well as with NHSE/I, in order to agree contracting arrangements with a range of external providers. Providers will be a mix of NHS, VCSE and independent sector. You will provide expert advice to senior colleagues on technical contractual issues and specific performance related information regarding existing contracts, attending board meetings as required to present relevant reports and updates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note any correspondence following application will be sent via trac.jobs &amp; the Trust&#39;s Resourcing Team**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Ives: sarah.ives5@nhs.net 07977030736&lt;/p&gt;
